summary: Minimal changes detected between the old and new content of the ACSC Information Security Manual (ISM).  The only discernible difference is a 1KB reduction in the size of the 'System security plan annex template' file, from 157KB to 156KB. The content of the manual itself appears identical.
analysis: A thorough comparison reveals virtually no substantive changes to the ACSC ISM document. The file size discrepancy in the annex template is insignificant and could be attributed to minor formatting adjustments or version control differences.  There are no apparent alterations to the main manual text, cybersecurity principles, guidelines, or terminology sections.
